race.comment: FLASHLIGHT (1) showed early speed from a good draw last time and battled on to finish sixth, beaten 2.5 lengths, over 1755m at Geelong. Comes back a notch here and will take plenty of catching. TRINITY'S D'ORO (7) is very consistent and has won two of her past three, too good in a BM56 at Hanging Rock last time out. Harder now but she sets up for every hope. SHE'S A CON (8) tackled a stronger race at Warrnambool last time out and struggled. She'll be better for that and hard to hold out. BELLADRAMATIC (10) struggled here second up  when in the market in a BM70. She can peak now and this looks easier. BROADHURST (12) is going okay and has each way claims again.
